e’s survival story is a painful reminder that only European Jews with significant financial means were able to carefully orchestrate an escape from Nazi Germany.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  aJapan, transiberian railway, Russia, holocaust, jewish, Nazi Germany, young girl.1 aListort, Darilyn Stahl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aListort, Dennis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStahl Listort, Darilyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771990639423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771990639/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles